AS INTRODUCED
6
7
An Act relating to income tax; providing tax credit
7
for teachers attaining certain years of service with
8
a school district; prescribing credit amount and
8
requirements; providing exception for certain
9
eligibility requirement; authorizing the Oklahoma Tax
9
Commission to conduct audit to determine eligibility;
10
requiring the recapture of credit if a taxpayer
10
becomes ineligible; making the credit refundable;
11
providing for codification; and providing an
11
effective date.
12
12
13
13
14
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14
15
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15
16
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2357.49 of Title 68, unless
16
17
there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17
18
A. For tax year 2027 and subsequent tax years, there shall be
18
19
allowed against the tax imposed by Section 2355 of Title 68 of the
19
20
Oklahoma Statutes, a credit for any individual who is certified to
20
21
teach in this state and has begun teaching an eighth consecutive
21
22
year in a school district in this state during the tax year. The
22
23
credit allowed shall be in the amount of Ten Thousand Dollars
23
24
($10,000.00).
24
Req. No. 2193 Page 1

1
B. Any taxpayer claiming the credit authorized by this section
1
2
shall continue to teach in the same school district for the
2
3
remainder of the eighth year, plus three (3) more consecutive years,
3
4
to remain eligible for the credit. Provided, if the taxpayer became
4
5
unemployed due to a reduction in force by the school district,
5
6
death, or a documented medical hardship, the taxpayer shall remain
6
7
eligible. The Commission may conduct an audit to verify the
7
8
eligibility of a taxpayer that has claimed the credit authorized
8
9
pursuant to this section. The Commission shall recapture the
9
10
credits otherwise authorized by the provisions of this section if an
10
11
audit conducted shows that the taxpayer became ineligible.
11
12
C. If the credit exceeds the tax imposed by Section 2355 of
12
13
Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the excess amount shall be
13
14
refunded to the taxpayer.
14
15
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
